The paper presents algorithms for graph problems in the Massively Parallel Computation (MPC) model, which is a distributed computing model. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are likely categories. The problems studied in the paper, namely maximal independent set, maximum matching, and minimum vertex cover, are classic problems in graph theory, so cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a likely category. The paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) may be a relevant category. Finally, the paper cites previous work on similar problems, which suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) may also be a relevant category.
